This article announces several appointments and nominations made by the United States government. The individuals mentioned include James J. Blanchard, who has been appointed as a Member of the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy, Tanya Monique Jones Bosier, who has been nominated as an Associate Judge of the Superior Court of the District of Columbia, Fara Damelin, who has been nominated as Inspector General of the Federal Communications Commission, Jeremy C. Daniel, who has been nominated as a United States District Judge for the Northern District of Illinois, Joel Ehrendreich, who has been nominated as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Palau, Brendan Abell Hurson and Matthew James Maddox, who have both been nominated as United States District Judges for the District of Maryland, Kara C. McDonald, who has been nominated as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Lithuania, Tara K. McGrath, who has been nominated as United States Attorney for the Southern District of California, Danny Lam Hoan Nguyen, who has been nominated as an Associate Judge of the Superior Court of the District of Columbia, Eric G. Olshan, who has been nominated as United States Attorney for the Western District of Pennsylvania, Darrel James Papillion, who has been nominated as United States District Judge for the Eastern District of Louisiana, John Joseph Sullivan, who has been nominated as a Member of the Board of Directors of the United States Institute of Peace, and Loren E. Sweatt, who has been nominated as a Member of the National Mediation Board.